msgctxt "sn13.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 13 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 13 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Abhisamayavagga "
msgstr "1. Comprehension "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn13.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Dutiyasambhejjaudakasutta "
msgstr "4. Where the Waters Flow Together (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.2"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge. "

# NOTE: Alas, not so theoretical any more: http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2016/may/18/india-set-to-start-massive-project-to-divert-ganges-and-brahmaputra-rivers
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.3"
msgid "gaṅgā yamunā aciravatī sarabhū mahī, taṃ udakaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya ṭhapetvā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni. "
msgstr "Suppose that water dried up and evaporated except for two or three drops. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.4:1.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn13.4:1.5"
msgid "katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ, yaṃ vā sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ yāni vā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti? "
msgstr "Which is more: the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, or the two or three drops left?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn13.4:2.1"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ sambhejjaudakaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ; "
msgstr "“Sir, the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated is certainly more. "

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.2"
msgid "appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhāni. "
msgstr "The two or three drops left are tiny. "

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.3"
msgid "Neva satimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na sahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti na satasahassimaṃ kalaṃ upenti sambhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādiṇṇaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti. "
msgstr "Compared to the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, it’s not nearly a hundredth, a thousandth, or a hundred thousandth part.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn13.4:2.4"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "“In the same way, for a noble disciple, the suffering that’s over and done with is more …” "

msgctxt "sn13.4:2.5"
msgid "dhammacakkhupaṭilābho”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn13.4:2.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

